# Testing and Quality Rules

No core gameplay change is complete without tests.

## Required Gameplay Tests

When touching battle logic, add or update tests for:
- valid match resolution
- invalid swap behavior
- move consumption
- resource generation
- AP generation
- max AP cap
- skill cost validation
- skill execution
- insufficient resource handling
- enemy turn resolution
- death/victory/defeat states
- status effects if involved

## Required Firebase Tests

When touching backend/security logic:
- use Firebase emulators where practical
- test allowed and denied Firestore paths
- test Cloud Function validation
- test reward idempotency
- test purchase/reward duplication prevention

## Commands

Run when practical:

```bash
dart format .
flutter analyze
flutter test
```

For backend work, inspect available scripts first. Do not assume npm scripts exist.

## Definition of Done

A change is not done unless:
- code is formatted
- analysis is clean or issues are documented
- relevant tests pass
- risky assumptions are called out
- no production deploy was performed without approval
